## Firestore Security Rules — Key Points

- **hospitals + doctors**: any signed-in user can read. Only owner or admin can write.
- **patients**: only owner or admin can read/write.
- **care_journeys + patient_documents**: only owner patient or admin.
- **doctor_slots booking**: any signed-in user can flip `available → false / status → reserved` on a slot that is still available. That is the only cross-user write allowed.
- **`isAdmin()`**: reads `/users/{uid}.role` inline — one extra Firestore read per admin-gated rule evaluation.
- **notifications**: admin writes only, owner reads only.

