## Gemini AI Functions (`src/services/gemini.ts`)

All use `gemini-2.5-flash`, `temperature: 0.2–0.4`. All called from the browser. API key: `VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY`.

| Function | Purpose | Called from |
|---|---|---|
| `triage(symptoms, patientContext?)` | Symptom → CareCategory JSON | Assess page |
| `analyzeDocument(file)` | Medical doc → structured analysis JSON | Documents page |
| `askAboutDocument(q, analysis, history)` | Q&A on an analyzed document | DocumentDetail |
| `generatePreVisitSummary(symptoms, triage, patient)` | Pre-visit summary for doctor | PreVisitSummary |
| `helpBotChat(message, history)` | Product help chat | HelpBot/Companion |
| `generateDoctorInsights(name, specialty, reasons)` | Practice insights for doctor | DoctorDashboard |
| `summary()` | Legacy alias for generatePreVisitSummary | — |

**Safety rules baked into every system prompt:**
- `triage()`: output MUST be one of 6 fixed categories. If not, `FALLBACK_TRIAGE` is returned (`URGENT_TODAY` + safe messaging).
- `analyzeDocument()`: never diagnoses, never changes meds, always includes disclaimer.
- `helpBotChat()`: if user asks anything clinical, returns fixed redirect text. Never guesses.

