## Specialty IDs — IMPORTANT

**Always use snake_case IDs in Firestore**, not display names. The `SPECIALTIES` array in `src/lib/specialties.ts` is the canonical list.

```
internal_medicine, family_medicine, pediatrics, cardiology, neurology, neurosurgery,
orthopedics, dermatology, dentistry, oral_surgery, obgyn, psychiatry, psychology,
ophthalmology, ent, urology, gastroenterology, endocrinology, oncology, pulmonology,
nephrology, rheumatology, emergency_medicine, radiology, anesthesiology, physical_therapy
```

`getSpecialtyLabel(id)` converts ID → display name. If the ID is not in the list it returns the raw string as a fallback.

ProviderResults has a `toSpecialtyId()` normalizer that converts display names → IDs to handle legacy Firestore data.

